      "61l9a": "From Greek agalma âstatue,â agalmatomancy divines omens in idolsâcracks in marble, sweat on bronze, or the way a wax effigy melts. Ancient Greeks watched temple statues that wept or bled; medieval magi cast soft figurines into water, reading the fissures to diagnose hidden malefice.",
