      "notes": "OverviewKoldovstoretz floats atop the frozen expanse of LakeÂ Ladoga, its iceâcarved citadel concealed by ancient spells of concealment and illusion. Founded in the 17thÂ century by exiled court magicians, it blends Russian baroque architecture with frostâwoven embellishments. Students arrive by enchanted iceâskates or sleigh, passing under onionâdomed towers crowned with crystalline spires. Renowned for its mastery of elemental and frost magic, Koldovstoretz draws the brightest from Russia, Eastern Europe, Scandinavia, and beyondâcompeting fiercely with Dobastrias to shape the continentâs next generation of sorcerers.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOccult Traditions\r\n\r\n\r\n \t\r\nDomovoi PactBinding household guardian spirits through hearthârite offerings and whispered oathsâprotecting concealed campuses and familiars.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nPerunâs Storm RiteStormâsummoning ceremonies invoking lightningâcharm sequences at midwinter, harnessing Perunâs power for defensive and offensive wards.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nKoldun BindingFrostâcraft rituals that lock ambient cold into talismans and armorâtempering iceâforged charms capable of shattering enchanted barriers.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nWater LibationsSeasonal offerings cast onto the ice in silver bowls to placate lake spirits and ensure safe passage for psychopomp processions and supply convoys.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nRunic SigilcraftInscribing preâChristian Slavic runes on metal, wood, or ice to amplify spellworkâteaching students to merge tradition with modern arcane theory.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nPsychopomp PassageNocturnal lantern rites guiding ancestral spirits across the frozen lakeâtraining in soulânavigation and protective escort enchantments.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nArchitecture\r\n\r\n\r\n \t\r\nFrostspire Turrets: Conical iceâlatticed towers that refract northern lights into the Great Hall by night.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nHearthway Gallery: A vaulted corridor lined with eternal braziersâhome to Domovoi alcoves and workshop for pactâbinding ceremonies.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nStorm Atrium: Openâroof courtyard ringed by stormâbells and lightning rods used in Perunâs Rite and elemental trials.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nIcebridge Causeways: Floating crystal pathways connecting lecture halls to living quartersâdissipating in spring and reforged each winter.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAreas ServedRussia; Ukraine; Belarus; Baltic States; Finland; Scandinavia; broader Eastern European magical communities",
      "notes-value": "<p class=\"\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"631\"><strong data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"12\">Overview</strong><br data-start=\"12\" data-end=\"15\" />Koldovstoretz floats atop the frozen expanse of LakeÂ Ladoga, its iceâcarved citadel concealed by ancient spells of concealment and illusion. Founded in the 17thÂ century by exiled court magicians, it blends Russian baroque architecture with frostâwoven embellishments. Students arrive by enchanted iceâskates or sleigh, passing under onionâdomed towers crowned with crystalline spires. Renowned for its mastery of elemental and frost magic, Koldovstoretz draws the brightest from Russia, Eastern Europe, Scandinavia, and beyondâcompeting fiercely with Dobastrias to shape the continentâs next generation of sorcerers.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"633\" data-end=\"636\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"638\" data-end=\"661\"><strong data-start=\"638\" data-end=\"659\">Occult Traditions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"662\" data-end=\"1667\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"662\" data-end=\"816\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"664\" data-end=\"816\"><strong data-start=\"664\" data-end=\"680\">Domovoi Pact</strong><br data-start=\"680\" data-end=\"683\" />Binding household guardian spirits through hearthârite offerings and whispered oathsâprotecting concealed campuses and familiars.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"817\" data-end=\"983\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"819\" data-end=\"983\"><strong data-start=\"819\" data-end=\"841\">Perunâs Storm Rite</strong><br data-start=\"841\" data-end=\"844\" />Stormâsummoning ceremonies invoking lightningâcharm sequences at midwinter, harnessing Perunâs power for defensive and offensive wards.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"984\" data-end=\"1148\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"986\" data-end=\"1148\"><strong data-start=\"986\" data-end=\"1004\">Koldun Binding</strong><br data-start=\"1004\" data-end=\"1007\" />Frostâcraft rituals that lock ambient cold into talismans and armorâtempering iceâforged charms capable of shattering enchanted barriers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1149\" data-end=\"1324\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1151\" data-end=\"1324\"><strong data-start=\"1151\" data-end=\"1170\">Water Libations</strong><br data-start=\"1170\" data-end=\"1173\" />Seasonal offerings cast onto the ice in silver bowls to placate lake spirits and ensure safe passage for psychopomp processions and supply convoys.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1325\" data-end=\"1499\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1327\" data-end=\"1499\"><strong data-start=\"1327\" data-end=\"1347\">Runic Sigilcraft</strong><br data-start=\"1347\" data-end=\"1350\" />Inscribing preâChristian Slavic runes on metal, wood, or ice to amplify spellworkâteaching students to merge tradition with modern arcane theory.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1500\" data-end=\"1667\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1502\" data-end=\"1667\"><strong data-start=\"1502\" data-end=\"1524\">Psychopomp Passage</strong><br data-start=\"1524\" data-end=\"1527\" />Nocturnal lantern rites guiding ancestral spirits across the frozen lakeâtraining in soulânavigation and protective escort enchantments.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1669\" data-end=\"1672\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1674\" data-end=\"1692\"><strong data-start=\"1674\" data-end=\"1690\">Architecture</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"1693\" data-end=\"2220\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1693\" data-end=\"1807\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1695\" data-end=\"1807\"><strong data-start=\"1695\" data-end=\"1718\">Frostspire Turrets:</strong> Conical iceâlatticed towers that refract northern lights into the Great Hall by night.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1808\" data-end=\"1947\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1810\" data-end=\"1947\"><strong data-start=\"1810\" data-end=\"1832\">Hearthway Gallery:</strong> A vaulted corridor lined with eternal braziersâhome to Domovoi alcoves and workshop for pactâbinding ceremonies.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1948\" data-end=\"2073\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"2073\"><strong data-start=\"1950\" data-end=\"1967\">Storm Atrium:</strong> Openâroof courtyard ringed by stormâbells and lightning rods used in Perunâs Rite and elemental trials.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2074\" data-end=\"2220\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2076\" data-end=\"2220\"><strong data-start=\"2076\" data-end=\"2100\">Icebridge Causeways:</strong> Floating crystal pathways connecting lecture halls to living quartersâdissipating in spring and reforged each winter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2222\" data-end=\"2225\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2227\" data-end=\"2353\"><strong data-start=\"2227\" data-end=\"2243\">Areas Served</strong><br data-start=\"2243\" data-end=\"2246\" />Russia; Ukraine; Belarus; Baltic States; Finland; Scandinavia; broader Eastern European magical communities</p>",
