      "notes-value": "<p class=\"\" data-start=\"120\" data-end=\"699\"><strong data-start=\"120\" data-end=\"132\">Overview</strong><br data-start=\"132\" data-end=\"135\" />Perched on a windswept promontory overlooking Galway Bay, Erehnoll specializes in the Healing Arts. Its whiteâwashed cloisters ring a central sacred spring, where students master herbal, ritual, and charmâbased cures. Under the guidance of <strong data-start=\"375\" data-end=\"393\">AnÂ SeachtÃºÂ Mac</strong> mentors and herbalâlore masters, apprentices combine dawnâtouch healing, <strong data-start=\"467\" data-end=\"490\">LeigheasÂ Luibheanna</strong> plantâwork, and <strong data-start=\"507\" data-end=\"516\">Ortha</strong> incantations. Graduates emerge as advanced healers, apothecary masters, or scholarly chroniclers of Irish folk medicineâsought across western Ireland and Celtic communities abroad.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"701\" data-end=\"704\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"706\" data-end=\"722\"><strong data-start=\"706\" data-end=\"720\">Traditions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"723\" data-end=\"1434\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"723\" data-end=\"870\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"725\" data-end=\"870\"><strong data-start=\"725\" data-end=\"743\">AnÂ SeachtÃºÂ Mac</strong><br data-start=\"743\" data-end=\"746\" />Seventhâson lineages teach the nineâstroke dawnâtouch cure, channeling innate restorative virtue through ritual contact.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"871\" data-end=\"1081\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"873\" data-end=\"1081\"><strong data-start=\"873\" data-end=\"896\">LeigheasÂ Luibheanna</strong><br data-start=\"896\" data-end=\"899\" />Intensive herbology seminars cover local <strong data-start=\"942\" data-end=\"956\">luibheanna</strong> (plants), harvesting at auspicious times, preparation of poultices, and working with each herbâs lifeâforce (<em data-start=\"1066\" data-end=\"1077\">fÃ©ar glas</em>).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1082\" data-end=\"1252\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1084\" data-end=\"1252\"><strong data-start=\"1084\" data-end=\"1104\">TobarÂ Beannaithe</strong><br data-start=\"1104\" data-end=\"1107\" />Fieldwork at holy wells trains students in <strong data-start=\"1152\" data-end=\"1163\">deiseal</strong> circuit rounds, clootieâtying, and using consecrated waters to cure stubborn ailments.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1253\" data-end=\"1434\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1255\" data-end=\"1434\"><strong data-start=\"1255\" data-end=\"1264\">Ortha</strong><br data-start=\"1264\" data-end=\"1267\" />Daily drills in spoken charmâcuresârhyming incantations for bleeding, fever, and spiritâblastsâblend Christian and preâChristian elements to command unseen forces.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1436\" data-end=\"1439\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1441\" data-end=\"1459\"><strong data-start=\"1441\" data-end=\"1457\">Architecture</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"1460\" data-end=\"2002\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1460\" data-end=\"1589\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1462\" data-end=\"1589\"><strong data-start=\"1462\" data-end=\"1489\">SpringâCloister Atrium:</strong> Central colonnade edged by hawthorn festooned with clooties, through which the sacred well flows.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1590\" data-end=\"1745\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1592\" data-end=\"1745\"><strong data-start=\"1592\" data-end=\"1617\">HerbâTerrace Gardens:</strong> Layered stone terraces planted with plantain (<em data-start=\"1664\" data-end=\"1673\">slanlus</em>), foxglove, and dandelionâeach plot marked by oghamâinscribed stones.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1746\" data-end=\"1871\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1748\" data-end=\"1871\"><strong data-start=\"1748\" data-end=\"1763\">Ortha Hall:</strong> Vaulted chamber lined with polished iron fonts where students recite incantations over consecrated water.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1872\" data-end=\"2002\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1874\" data-end=\"2002\"><strong data-start=\"1874\" data-end=\"1900\">HealingâLight Gallery:</strong> Ribbon of eastâfacing archways floods the infirmary and incantation chamber with dawnâs first rays.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2004\" data-end=\"2007\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2009\" data-end=\"2140\"><strong data-start=\"2009\" data-end=\"2025\">Areas Served</strong><br data-start=\"2025\" data-end=\"2028\" />County Galway; Mayo; Sligo; Leitrim; Donegal; Celticâheritage communities in western Scotland and Newfoundland</p>",
