      "notes-value": "<strong data-start=\"121\" data-end=\"133\">Overview</strong><br data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"136\" />Perched on a windswept ridge above the Yarlung Tsangpo valley, LiÂ De draws on millennia of Tibetan artisanship to forge wards and talismans of unmatched potency. Its graniteâwalled workshops overlook prayerâflagâdraped passes, while resident ngakpa lineages tutor students in both handsâon crafting and visionary ritual. Renowned across the Himalaya for protective amulets that safeguard highâaltitude caravans, LiÂ De blends mountainâborn endurance with subtleâbody alchemy.\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"619\" data-end=\"635\"><strong data-start=\"619\" data-end=\"633\">Traditions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"636\" data-end=\"1577\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"636\" data-end=\"814\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"638\" data-end=\"814\"><strong data-start=\"638\" data-end=\"655\">MdosÂ /Â Namkha</strong><br data-start=\"655\" data-end=\"658\" />Daily weaving of coloredâyarn threadâcrosses (namkha) instills cosmic harmony and precision in every knot, anchoring protective spells in material form.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"815\" data-end=\"1021\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"817\" data-end=\"1021\"><strong data-start=\"817\" data-end=\"825\">Glud</strong><br data-start=\"825\" data-end=\"828\" />Crafting and ceremonially dispatching effigy replicas teaches the art of spiritual reciprocityâstudents learn how symbolic âransomâ offerings restore balance to a stolen or fragmented soul.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1022\" data-end=\"1195\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1024\" data-end=\"1195\"><strong data-start=\"1024\" data-end=\"1033\">Tummo</strong><br data-start=\"1033\" data-end=\"1036\" />Esoteric innerâfire yoga breathâwork channels geothermal heat into the body, empowering students to temper metals and infuse wards with living heatâenergy.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1196\" data-end=\"1383\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1198\" data-end=\"1383\"><strong data-start=\"1198\" data-end=\"1218\">TulpaÂ /Â Sprulâpa</strong><br data-start=\"1218\" data-end=\"1221\" />Sustained visualization exercises train adepts to generate thoughtâforms that animate talismans, sharpening mental focus and intentionality in every artifact.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1384\" data-end=\"1577\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1386\" data-end=\"1577\"><strong data-start=\"1386\" data-end=\"1398\">RoâLangs</strong><br data-start=\"1398\" data-end=\"1401\" />Corpseâbinding drills mimic the stiffâjointed revenants of rural lore, equipping novices with the mantraâinfused techniques needed to sculpt and seal undeadâwarding charms.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1579\" data-end=\"1582\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1584\" data-end=\"1602\"><strong data-start=\"1584\" data-end=\"1600\">Architecture</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"1603\" data-end=\"2141\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1603\" data-end=\"1732\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1605\" data-end=\"1732\"><strong data-start=\"1605\" data-end=\"1627\">Rockâhewn Atelier:</strong> Four cliffâside workspaces carved into roseâtinted granite, each crowned by a suspended namkha mobile.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1733\" data-end=\"1860\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1735\" data-end=\"1860\"><strong data-start=\"1735\" data-end=\"1763\">Geothermal Furnace Hall:</strong> A domed chamber fed by subterranean hot springs, where Tummoâheated forges temper metal wards.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1861\" data-end=\"2011\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1863\" data-end=\"2011\"><strong data-start=\"1863\" data-end=\"1884\">Mandala Skylight:</strong> Central courtyard ringed by stainedâglass panels depicting Sprulâpa mandalas, channeling sunlight onto the crafting benches.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2012\" data-end=\"2141\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2014\" data-end=\"2141\"><strong data-start=\"2014\" data-end=\"2035\">Wardstone FaÃ§ade:</strong> Fortified gate flanked by colossal RoâLangsâwarding statuesâstone effigies imbued with sealing mantras.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2143\" data-end=\"2146\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2148\" data-end=\"2315\"><strong data-start=\"2148\" data-end=\"2164\">Areas Served</strong><br data-start=\"2164\" data-end=\"2167\" />Tibet Autonomous Region (China); western Sichuan highlands; northern Bhutan; Nepalese transâHimalayan valleys; northern Indian Himalayan foothills</p>",
