      "canon": "Yes",
      "notes": "Overview\r\nThe Charms School is renowned for its bareâbones, focused approach to magical trainingâspecifically in the art of casting charms. Located in London, this institution offers a noânonsense curriculum designed to instill precision, discipline, and technical mastery in every student. Its straightforward approach means that every lesson is geared toward honing the skills needed for effective charm-casting, backed up by essential studies in Runes, History, and Arithmancy.\r\n\r\nIntegrated Occult Traditions\r\nDrawing on centuriesâold British magical practices, the schoolâs integrated traditions are woven through every subject area, creating a unified framework for focused learning:\r\n\r\n\r\n \t\r\nAnglo-Saxon Charmcraft:Rooted in early medieval manuscripts and ritual lore, this tradition emphasizes the clarity and precision of spellcasting as recorded in the Exeter Book and other historical texts. It insists on discipline and subtlety, stripping away extraneous flourish.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nRunic Clarity:This tradition draws upon authentic ancient runic practices from AngloâSaxon and Celtic sources, teaching students that effective magic is built upon a firm, unobscured understanding of the symbolic language of old.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nNumerical Resonance:Grounded in early forms of arithmantic thought, this approach integrates the mysticism of numbers with the mechanics of spell patterns. It helps practitioners see magic as a structured, almost mathematical art, ensuring that every incantation aligns with an underlying numerical order.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nChronicles of the Arcane:Focusing on factual, rigorous examination of magical history, this tradition eschews myth for wellâdocumented evolution. It encourages students to engage with primary sources and authentic records of the development of charmcraft throughout British history.\r\n\r\n\r\nTogether, these traditions form a disciplined, historically informed foundation that permeates every aspect of the schoolâs curriculum.\r\n\r\nArchitecture\r\nThe Charms School is housed in a modest, purposeâbuilt facility in London, reflecting its emphasis on focus over flash. Classrooms, practical labs, and study halls are designed for efficiency, with clean lines, minimal decoration, and plenty of space for handsâon practice. The straightforward design reinforces the school's philosophy: that mastery comes not from ornate surroundings but from rigorous practice and clear thought.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAreas Served\r\nThe school draws students from throughout London and across the United Kingdom, particularly appealing to those who appreciate an unadorned and disciplined approach to magical education. Its reputation for producing highly skilled charm-casters has made it a soughtâafter destination for aspiring wizards who value technical precision and a focused, academic environment.",
      "notes-value": "<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"53\" data-end=\"65\">Overview</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"67\" data-end=\"537\">The Charms School is renowned for its bareâbones, focused approach to magical trainingâspecifically in the art of casting charms. Located in London, this institution offers a noânonsense curriculum designed to instill precision, discipline, and technical mastery in every student. Its straightforward approach means that every lesson is geared toward honing the skills needed for effective charm-casting, backed up by essential studies in Runes, History, and Arithmancy.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"544\" data-end=\"576\">Integrated Occult Traditions</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"578\" data-end=\"753\">Drawing on centuriesâold British magical practices, the schoolâs integrated traditions are woven through every subject area, creating a unified framework for focused learning:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"755\" data-end=\"1899\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"755\" data-end=\"1044\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"757\" data-end=\"1044\"><strong data-start=\"757\" data-end=\"784\">Anglo-Saxon Charmcraft:</strong><br data-start=\"784\" data-end=\"787\" />Rooted in early medieval manuscripts and ritual lore, this tradition emphasizes the clarity and precision of spellcasting as recorded in the Exeter Book and other historical texts. It insists on discipline and subtlety, stripping away extraneous flourish.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1046\" data-end=\"1286\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1048\" data-end=\"1286\"><strong data-start=\"1048\" data-end=\"1066\">Runic Clarity:</strong><br data-start=\"1066\" data-end=\"1069\" />This tradition draws upon authentic ancient runic practices from AngloâSaxon and Celtic sources, teaching students that effective magic is built upon a firm, unobscured understanding of the symbolic language of old.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1288\" data-end=\"1604\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1290\" data-end=\"1604\"><strong data-start=\"1290\" data-end=\"1314\">Numerical Resonance:</strong><br data-start=\"1314\" data-end=\"1317\" />Grounded in early forms of arithmantic thought, this approach integrates the mysticism of numbers with the mechanics of spell patterns. It helps practitioners see magic as a structured, almost mathematical art, ensuring that every incantation aligns with an underlying numerical order.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1606\" data-end=\"1899\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1608\" data-end=\"1899\"><strong data-start=\"1608\" data-end=\"1637\">Chronicles of the Arcane:</strong><br data-start=\"1637\" data-end=\"1640\" />Focusing on factual, rigorous examination of magical history, this tradition eschews myth for wellâdocumented evolution. It encourages students to engage with primary sources and authentic records of the development of charmcraft throughout British history.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1901\" data-end=\"2036\">Together, these traditions form a disciplined, historically informed foundation that permeates every aspect of the schoolâs curriculum.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2043\" data-end=\"2059\">Architecture</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2061\" data-end=\"2491\">The Charms School is housed in a modest, purposeâbuilt facility in London, reflecting its emphasis on focus over flash. Classrooms, practical labs, and study halls are designed for efficiency, with clean lines, minimal decoration, and plenty of space for handsâon practice. The straightforward design reinforces the school's philosophy: that mastery comes not from ornate surroundings but from rigorous practice and clear thought.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2493\" data-end=\"2496\" />\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2498\" data-end=\"2514\">Areas Served</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2516\" data-end=\"2887\">The school draws students from throughout London and across the United Kingdom, particularly appealing to those who appreciate an unadorned and disciplined approach to magical education. Its reputation for producing highly skilled charm-casters has made it a soughtâafter destination for aspiring wizards who value technical precision and a focused, academic environment.</p>",
