      "location": "Bolivian Salt Flats",
      "notes": "Iasivia IeblesNestled along the edge of the Bolivian Salt Flats\r\nOverviewIasivia Iebles is a singular institution renowned for its intensive focus on divination. Set against the vast, shimmering expanse of the Bolivian Salt Flatsâwhere the reflective surfaces are believed to enhance magical sightâthe school offers a sevenâyear curriculum covering Charms, Potions, Alchemy, Divination, Transfiguration, Herbology, and History. In this environment, every lesson is steeped in the belief that the land itself reveals hidden truths.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTraditions\r\n\r\n\r\n \t\r\nSalar Vision:This tradition draws inspiration from the salt flatsâ mirrorâlike surfaces, which are said to sharpen sight and awaken intuitive insight. Salar Vision not only underpins the Divination course but also influences Charms and Transfiguration by emphasizing clarity and reflection in magic.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nAndean Spirit Weave:Rooted in indigenous Andean practices, Andean Spirit Weave celebrates the intimate connection between the people and the natural world. It guides Herbology and History by preserving ancient lore and infusing Potions with the rhythm of local herbal life.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nCrystalline Alchemy:Inspired by the brilliant mineral formations interlaced among the salt deposits, Crystalline Alchemy teaches the art of transformation. This tradition is key to both Alchemy and Transfiguration, highlighting how raw elements may be refined into magical substances.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nSalt Seerâs Legacy:A divinatory art unique to these salt flats, Salt Seerâs Legacy uses the reflective quality of salt to foretell the future. Its influence is most potent in Divination, while also lending its perspective to the practice of Charms.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nArchitectureThe campus of Iasivia Iebles is a study in contrastsâits structures echo the otherworldly beauty of the salt flats. Salt-infused stone walls refract sunlight into dazzling patterns across vast open courtyards and meditative terraces. Designed to encourage visionary contemplation, the schoolâs halls feature large reflective surfaces that enhance divinatory practice. The use of natural light, together with carefully positioned alcoves and open solariums, creates an environment where magic and the landscape blend seamlessly.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAreas ServedIasivia Iebles welcomes students from all over Bolivia and from the surrounding Andean regions. Its diverse community includes inhabitants of highland villages, urban centers, and indigenous groupsâall united by a shared belief in the power of the salt flats to reveal hidden truths.",
      "notes-value": "<p class=\"\" data-start=\"267\" data-end=\"339\"><strong data-start=\"267\" data-end=\"285\">Iasivia Iebles</strong><br data-start=\"285\" data-end=\"288\" /><em data-start=\"288\" data-end=\"339\">Nestled along the edge of the Bolivian Salt Flats</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"341\" data-end=\"813\"><strong data-start=\"341\" data-end=\"353\">Overview</strong><br data-start=\"353\" data-end=\"356\" />Iasivia Iebles is a singular institution renowned for its intensive focus on divination. Set against the vast, shimmering expanse of the Bolivian Salt Flatsâwhere the reflective surfaces are believed to enhance magical sightâthe school offers a sevenâyear curriculum covering Charms, Potions, Alchemy, Divination, Transfiguration, Herbology, and History. In this environment, every lesson is steeped in the belief that the land itself reveals hidden truths.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"815\" data-end=\"818\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"820\" data-end=\"834\"><strong data-start=\"820\" data-end=\"834\">Traditions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul data-start=\"836\" data-end=\"1990\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"836\" data-end=\"1146\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"838\" data-end=\"1146\"><strong data-start=\"838\" data-end=\"855\">Salar Vision:</strong><br data-start=\"855\" data-end=\"858\" />This tradition draws inspiration from the salt flatsâ mirrorâlike surfaces, which are said to sharpen sight and awaken intuitive insight. Salar Vision not only underpins the Divination course but also influences Charms and Transfiguration by emphasizing clarity and reflection in magic.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1148\" data-end=\"1432\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1150\" data-end=\"1432\"><strong data-start=\"1150\" data-end=\"1174\">Andean Spirit Weave:</strong><br data-start=\"1174\" data-end=\"1177\" />Rooted in indigenous Andean practices, Andean Spirit Weave celebrates the intimate connection between the people and the natural world. It guides Herbology and History by preserving ancient lore and infusing Potions with the rhythm of local herbal life.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1434\" data-end=\"1729\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1436\" data-end=\"1729\"><strong data-start=\"1436\" data-end=\"1460\">Crystalline Alchemy:</strong><br data-start=\"1460\" data-end=\"1463\" />Inspired by the brilliant mineral formations interlaced among the salt deposits, Crystalline Alchemy teaches the art of transformation. This tradition is key to both Alchemy and Transfiguration, highlighting how raw elements may be refined into magical substances.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1731\" data-end=\"1990\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1733\" data-end=\"1990\"><strong data-start=\"1733\" data-end=\"1756\">Salt Seerâs Legacy:</strong><br data-start=\"1756\" data-end=\"1759\" />A divinatory art unique to these salt flats, Salt Seerâs Legacy uses the reflective quality of salt to foretell the future. Its influence is most potent in Divination, while also lending its perspective to the practice of Charms.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"1992\" data-end=\"1995\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1997\" data-end=\"2543\"><strong data-start=\"1997\" data-end=\"2013\">Architecture</strong><br data-start=\"2013\" data-end=\"2016\" />The campus of Iasivia Iebles is a study in contrastsâits structures echo the otherworldly beauty of the salt flats. Salt-infused stone walls refract sunlight into dazzling patterns across vast open courtyards and meditative terraces. Designed to encourage visionary contemplation, the schoolâs halls feature large reflective surfaces that enhance divinatory practice. The use of natural light, together with carefully positioned alcoves and open solariums, creates an environment where magic and the landscape blend seamlessly.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2545\" data-end=\"2548\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2550\" data-end=\"2852\"><strong data-start=\"2550\" data-end=\"2566\">Areas Served</strong><br data-start=\"2566\" data-end=\"2569\" />Iasivia Iebles welcomes students from all over Bolivia and from the surrounding Andean regions. Its diverse community includes inhabitants of highland villages, urban centers, and indigenous groupsâall united by a shared belief in the power of the salt flats to reveal hidden truths.</p>",
