      "notes": "Glacleaqiax School of MagicCarved into the marble heart of Ultimate Esperanza, Patagonia\r\nOverviewGlacleaqiax is a grand wizarding academy set within an immense Patagonian mountain. Its campus winds through ancient marble caves, where shadowed corridors and vaulted chambers echo centuries of lore. Dramatic outcroppings of the castle burst from the rock, most notably the world-renowned astronomy tower crowning the peak and gazing into the vast southern skies. In Years 1â2, every student is introduced to a core curriculum comprising Flying, Perception, History, Social Skills, Astronomy, and Creatures. From Years 3â7, the focus shifts to core courses in Perception, History, Social Skills, Astronomy, and Creatures, with electives available in Charms, Defense, Potions, Flying, and Transfiguration.\r\nTraditions\r\nMapuche Cosmovision:Celebrates the deep interconnectedness of community, nature, and ancestral spirit. Its ancient narratives shape History courses and inform ritual gestures in advanced magical theory, ensuring that each lesson in History resonates with the wisdom of the Mapuche.\r\nTehuelche Celestial Lore:Honors the cosmic dance of the southern skies, where every star is believed to guide destiny. This tradition is the bedrock of Astronomy instructionâlinking celestial events to historical cyclesâand enriches History with cosmic symbolism.\r\nMarble Echo Mysticism:Rooted in reverence for the marble caves that define the campus, this tradition sees stone as the silent keeper of memory. It informs History through study of ancient inscriptions and lends a mystical perspective to Creature studies, revealing how the local fauna embody the mountainâs storied spirit.\r\nAuroral Alchemy:Harnesses the transformative energy of natural minerals and breathtaking auroras. Its principles underpin both Potions and Transfiguration, teaching that change and refinement are as intrinsic as the shifting light across the mountain peaks.\r\nGranite Sentinel Doctrine:Draws inspiration from the mountainâs unyielding granite to forge powerful defenses. Its tenets guide Defense curriculum, instilling resilience and mastery over protective enchantments that mirror the enduring strength of Patagoniaâs rugged landscape.\r\nArchitectureGlacleaqiaxâs campus is a spellbinding blend of natural wonder and deliberate design. The majority of the school is hewn directly into the ancient marble of Ultimate Esperanza, with hidden corridors and vast, vaulted chambers that preserve the lore of millennia. Strategic outcroppings allow natural light to illuminate select halls, culminating in the breathtaking astronomy tower that crowns the mountainâs peakâa beacon that invites students to unlock the secrets of the cosmos.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAreas ServedGlacleaqiax proudly serves a diverse community drawn from across Patagonia and southern South America. Its students hail from indigenous communities, remote frontier settlements, and modern urban centers, each united by a deep reverence for the mountainâs ancient magic and the celestial tapestry overhead.",
      "notes-value": "<p class=\"\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"95\"><strong data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"31\">Glacleaqiax School of Magic</strong><br data-start=\"31\" data-end=\"34\" />Carved into the marble heart of Ultimate Esperanza, Patagonia</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"97\" data-end=\"817\"><strong data-start=\"97\" data-end=\"109\">Overview</strong><br data-start=\"109\" data-end=\"112\" />Glacleaqiax is a grand wizarding academy set within an immense Patagonian mountain. Its campus winds through ancient marble caves, where shadowed corridors and vaulted chambers echo centuries of lore. Dramatic outcroppings of the castle burst from the rock, most notably the world-renowned astronomy tower crowning the peak and gazing into the vast southern skies. In Years 1â2, every student is introduced to a core curriculum comprising Flying, Perception, History, Social Skills, Astronomy, and Creatures. From Years 3â7, the focus shifts to core courses in Perception, History, Social Skills, Astronomy, and Creatures, with electives available in Charms, Defense, Potions, Flying, and Transfiguration.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"824\" data-end=\"838\"><strong data-start=\"824\" data-end=\"838\">Traditions</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"840\" data-end=\"1128\"><strong data-start=\"840\" data-end=\"864\">Mapuche Cosmovision:</strong><br data-start=\"864\" data-end=\"867\" />Celebrates the deep interconnectedness of community, nature, and ancestral spirit. Its ancient narratives shape History courses and inform ritual gestures in advanced magical theory, ensuring that each lesson in History resonates with the wisdom of the Mapuche.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1130\" data-end=\"1400\"><strong data-start=\"1130\" data-end=\"1159\">Tehuelche Celestial Lore:</strong><br data-start=\"1159\" data-end=\"1162\" />Honors the cosmic dance of the southern skies, where every star is believed to guide destiny. This tradition is the bedrock of Astronomy instructionâlinking celestial events to historical cyclesâand enriches History with cosmic symbolism.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1402\" data-end=\"1732\"><strong data-start=\"1402\" data-end=\"1428\">Marble Echo Mysticism:</strong><br data-start=\"1428\" data-end=\"1431\" />Rooted in reverence for the marble caves that define the campus, this tradition sees stone as the silent keeper of memory. It informs History through study of ancient inscriptions and lends a mystical perspective to Creature studies, revealing how the local fauna embody the mountainâs storied spirit.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1734\" data-end=\"1998\"><strong data-start=\"1734\" data-end=\"1754\">Auroral Alchemy:</strong><br data-start=\"1754\" data-end=\"1757\" />Harnesses the transformative energy of natural minerals and breathtaking auroras. Its principles underpin both Potions and Transfiguration, teaching that change and refinement are as intrinsic as the shifting light across the mountain peaks.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2000\" data-end=\"2284\"><strong data-start=\"2000\" data-end=\"2030\">Granite Sentinel Doctrine:</strong><br data-start=\"2030\" data-end=\"2033\" />Draws inspiration from the mountainâs unyielding granite to forge powerful defenses. Its tenets guide Defense curriculum, instilling resilience and mastery over protective enchantments that mirror the enduring strength of Patagoniaâs rugged landscape.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2291\" data-end=\"2791\"><strong data-start=\"2291\" data-end=\"2307\">Architecture</strong><br data-start=\"2307\" data-end=\"2310\" />Glacleaqiaxâs campus is a spellbinding blend of natural wonder and deliberate design. The majority of the school is hewn directly into the ancient marble of Ultimate Esperanza, with hidden corridors and vast, vaulted chambers that preserve the lore of millennia. Strategic outcroppings allow natural light to illuminate select halls, culminating in the breathtaking astronomy tower that crowns the mountainâs peakâa beacon that invites students to unlock the secrets of the cosmos.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr class=\"\" data-start=\"2793\" data-end=\"2796\" />\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2798\" data-end=\"3123\"><strong data-start=\"2798\" data-end=\"2814\">Areas Served</strong><br data-start=\"2814\" data-end=\"2817\" />Glacleaqiax proudly serves a diverse community drawn from across Patagonia and southern South America. Its students hail from indigenous communities, remote frontier settlements, and modern urban centers, each united by a deep reverence for the mountainâs ancient magic and the celestial tapestry overhead.</p>",
