      "notes": "Cuamiatte School of Magic\r\nThabaâTseka Highlands, Lesotho â Southern Africaâs premier defensive academy\r\n\r\nOverview\r\nPerched on a windswept ridge above 2â¯800â¯m, Cuamiatte trains witches and wizards to turn mountain, weather, and starlight into living shields. Every student follows the same sixâsubject programmeâCharms, Defense, Potions, Transfiguration, History, Astronomyâfrom first incantation to mastery; no electives are offered.\r\n\r\nPhilosophyÂ âÂ âThe Mountain Yields, the Mountain Guardsâ\r\n\r\n \t\r\nEndurance First â Spells, brews, and stances are judged by how long they hold under mountain pressure.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nWeather as Wall â Students learn to bend wind, cloud, and lightning into layered defenses.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nStoneâRooted Focus â Stable footing and slow, precise wand arcs mirror the immovable basalt beneath their feet.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nStarâTimed Readiness â All drills follow the highâaltitude star calendar; no shield rises out of rhythm with the sky.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nHistory as Warning â Cliffâpainted spirit guardians and past drought sieges are dissected so future defenders act faster and wiser.\r\n\r\n\r\nArchitectureÂ (Concise)\r\n\r\n \t\r\nShield Court â an oval, stoneâflagged arena sunk into the ridge for daily dawn Defense bouts.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nStormâTower Observatory â a basalt spire with a sliding roof for night astronomy and lightningârod charm practice.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nRondavel Row â thickâwalled stone classrooms and dorms whose outer faces double as test targets for reinforcement charms.\r\n\r\n \t\r\nFerment Caves â cool caverns beneath the ridge where longâbrew potions mature in clay amphorae beside drying racks of highâveld herbs.\r\n\r\n\r\nAreasâ¯Served\r\nMost students come from Lesotho, South Africaâs highland provinces, Eswatini, and southern Mozambique, with smaller cohorts from Zimbabwe and Namibia seeking elite defensive training.",
      "notes-value": "<h2 class=\"\" data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"30\">Cuamiatte School of Magic</h2>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"31\" data-end=\"109\"><em data-start=\"31\" data-end=\"109\">ThabaâTseka Highlands, Lesotho â Southern Africaâs premier defensive academy</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"116\" data-end=\"130\">Overview</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"131\" data-end=\"453\">Perched on a windswept ridge above 2â¯800â¯m, Cuamiatte trains witches and wizards to turn mountain, weather, and starlight into living shields. Every student follows the same sixâsubject programmeâ<strong data-start=\"327\" data-end=\"392\">Charms, Defense, Potions, Transfiguration, History, Astronomy</strong>âfrom first incantation to mastery; no electives are offered.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"1492\" data-end=\"1557\">PhilosophyÂ âÂ â<strong data-start=\"1510\" data-end=\"1554\">The Mountain Yields, the Mountain Guards</strong>â</h3>\r\n<ol data-start=\"1558\" data-end=\"2156\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1558\" data-end=\"1669\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1561\" data-end=\"1669\"><strong data-start=\"1561\" data-end=\"1580\">Endurance First</strong> â Spells, brews, and stances are judged by how long they hold under mountain pressure.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1670\" data-end=\"1769\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1673\" data-end=\"1769\"><strong data-start=\"1673\" data-end=\"1692\">Weather as Wall</strong> â Students learn to bend wind, cloud, and lightning into layered defenses.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1770\" data-end=\"1890\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1773\" data-end=\"1890\"><strong data-start=\"1773\" data-end=\"1795\">StoneâRooted Focus</strong> â Stable footing and slow, precise wand arcs mirror the immovable basalt beneath their feet.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"1891\" data-end=\"2017\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"1894\" data-end=\"2017\"><strong data-start=\"1894\" data-end=\"1918\">StarâTimed Readiness</strong> â All drills follow the highâaltitude star calendar; no shield rises out of rhythm with the sky.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2018\" data-end=\"2156\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2021\" data-end=\"2156\"><strong data-start=\"2021\" data-end=\"2043\">History as Warning</strong> â Cliffâpainted spirit guardians and past drought sieges are dissected so future defenders act faster and wiser.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2163\" data-end=\"2191\">ArchitectureÂ (Concise)</h3>\r\n<ul data-start=\"2192\" data-end=\"2687\">\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2192\" data-end=\"2293\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2194\" data-end=\"2293\"><strong data-start=\"2194\" data-end=\"2210\">Shield Court</strong> â an oval, stoneâflagged arena sunk into the ridge for daily dawn Defense bouts.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2294\" data-end=\"2416\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2296\" data-end=\"2416\"><strong data-start=\"2296\" data-end=\"2323\">StormâTower Observatory</strong> â a basalt spire with a sliding roof for night astronomy and lightningârod charm practice.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2417\" data-end=\"2546\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2419\" data-end=\"2546\"><strong data-start=\"2419\" data-end=\"2435\">Rondavel Row</strong> â thickâwalled stone classrooms and dorms whose outer faces double as test targets for reinforcement charms.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n \t<li class=\"\" data-start=\"2547\" data-end=\"2687\">\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2549\" data-end=\"2687\"><strong data-start=\"2549\" data-end=\"2566\">Ferment Caves</strong> â cool caverns beneath the ridge where longâbrew potions mature in clay amphorae beside drying racks of highâveld herbs.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class=\"\" data-start=\"2694\" data-end=\"2712\">Areasâ¯Served</h3>\r\n<p class=\"\" data-start=\"2713\" data-end=\"2896\">Most students come from Lesotho, South Africaâs highland provinces, Eswatini, and southern Mozambique, with smaller cohorts from Zimbabwe and Namibia seeking elite defensive training.</p>",
