      "description": "The Ashwinder was a thin pale-greyÂ snakeÂ with glowing red eyes. They rose from the dying embers of magicalÂ fire (like floo powder) that had been allowed to burn unchecked and unsupervised. Once birthed, the Ashwinder slithered off into a dark corner to lay their eggs, leaving an ashy trail behind. Ashwinders only lived for an hour and collapsed to dust when they have laid their eggs.[1]\r\nAshwinder eggsÂ were red and give off an intense heat. The heat was capable of igniting a dwelling within minutes of their birth.Â WizardsÂ suspecting the presence of Ashwinders in a house had to immediate track down the nest andÂ freezeÂ them using an appropriateÂ spell. Once frozen, Ashwinder eggs were very valuable; they could be used in aÂ love potions, eaten whole as a cure forÂ ague, or one batch could be used for theÂ Edurus Potion.",
      "description-value": "<p>The Ashwinder was a thin pale-greyÂ <a title=\"Snake\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Snake\">snake</a>Â with glowing red eyes. They rose from the dying embers of magicalÂ <a title=\"Fire\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Fire\">fire</a> (like floo powder) that had been allowed to burn unchecked and unsupervised. Once birthed, the Ashwinder slithered off into a dark corner to lay their <a title=\"Ashwinder egg\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ashwinder_egg\">eggs</a>, leaving an ashy trail behind. Ashwinders only lived for an hour and collapsed to dust when they have laid their eggs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FBR_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ashwinder#cite_note-FBR-1\">[1]</a></sup></p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Ashwinder egg\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ashwinder_egg\">Ashwinder eggs</a>Â were red and give off an intense heat. The heat was capable of igniting a dwelling within minutes of their birth.Â <a title=\"Wizardkind\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Wizardkind\">Wizards</a>Â suspecting the presence of Ashwinders in a house had to immediate track down the nest andÂ <a title=\"Freezing Spell\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Freezing_Spell\">freeze</a>Â them using an appropriateÂ <a title=\"Spell\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Spell\">spell</a>. Once frozen, Ashwinder eggs were very valuable; they could be used in aÂ <a title=\"Love potion\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Love_potion\">love potions</a>, eaten whole as a cure forÂ <a title=\"Ague\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Ague\">ague</a>, or one batch could be used for theÂ <a title=\"Edurus Potion\" href=\"https://harrypotter.fandom.com/wiki/Edurus_Potion\">Edurus Potion</a>.</p>",
